         <abstract id="aspace_261228ff60c8c68a4f3600fda0562ec5">The collection consists of clippings, printed and near-print materials, photographs and other papers concerning the Field family of Stockbridge, Massachusetts. Family members figuring prominently in this collection include Cyrus West Field (1819-1892) and David Dudley Field (1805-1894).</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <famname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85048104"
                     source="lcsh">
               <part>Field family</part>
            </famname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_bdc567fec23652b9f06544f98fc6bd67">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The papers were removed from the Brewer Family Papers, MS99; and were the gift of Diane Druin Gravlee, 1992.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
